headline: Why Williams-Sonoma Rallied 28.2% in November
summary: Shares of home goods retailer Williams Sonoma (NYSE: WSM) rallied 28.2% in November, according to data from S&P Global Market Intelligence.  Williams-Sonoma reported third-quarter results on Nov. 20, with shares skyrocketing in the aftermath, accounting for most of the month's gains.  Williams-Sonoma is a specialty retailer that owns several high-end home goods brands, including its Williams-Sonoma namesake, Pottery Barn, Pottery Barn Kids, West Elm, and Rejuvenation.
